FROM qwen2.5:latest

# ── Context ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Doubled from default 32768 → 65536.
# Browser pages with large DOM trees can have 200+ elements in the accessibility
# map. More context = agent sees the full page, not a truncated version.
PARAMETER num_ctx 65536

# ── Sampling — deterministic, precise tool calls ───────────────────────────────
# Temperature 0: no randomness. Browser actions must be correct every time.
# A stochastic model might click element 12 instead of 11 due to sampling noise.
PARAMETER temperature 0

# Keep only the top 20 token candidates — tight focus, fewer hallucinations.
PARAMETER top_k 20

# Nucleus sampling: only consider tokens comprising top 90% of probability mass.
PARAMETER top_p 0.9

# Penalise repetition — stops the model looping the same action endlessly.
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.15
PARAMETER repeat_last_n 64

# Cap output length. Browser actions are short JSON, not essays.
# Keeps latency low between steps.
PARAMETER num_predict 512

# ── System prompt ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pre-baked into the model so every conversation starts with browser context.
# browser-use overrides this per-task, but this ensures fallback behaviour is sane.
SYSTEM """You are a precise browser automation agent. Your job is to control a real web browser on behalf of the user.

You will receive:
- The user's goal
- A numbered list of interactive elements currently visible on the page
- The current page URL and title

You must respond with a single tool call to take the next action toward the goal. 

Rules:
- Always choose the most direct action toward the goal
- Prefer clicking visible elements over navigating by URL
- If a login page appears and you have credentials, fill them in
- If you are unsure which element to use, pick the most likely one and proceed
- Never repeat the same failed action more than twice — try a different approach
- When the goal is complete, call the done() tool with a summary of what was accomplished
- Be concise in your reasoning — one sentence maximum before the tool call"""
